  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Third-Party Risk Management Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the company</strong><br />A newly created role due to business expansion, with our client who is a leading diversified financial services group with an extensive regional footprint across Asia. <br /> <br /><strong>About the job</strong></p><p>Join an elite finance and governance division to spearhead complex risk mitigation strategies and enhance third-party performance across the business.</p><ul><li><p>Design and refine comprehensive frameworks to manage third-party-risks and group-level outsourcing.</p></li><li><p>Act as a primary consultant for internal business units to ensure high-risk engagements meet all regulatory and internal control standards.</p></li><li><p>Oversee the integrity of governance data and lead the continuous improvement of risk assessment tools.</p></li><li><p>Facilitate executive-level governance meetings by synthesizing risk data into actionable strategic insights.</p></li><li><p>Optimize sourcing processes for corporate indirect spend categories to improve return on investment and operational agility.</p></li></ul><p><br /> <br /><strong>Skills and experience required</strong></p><ul><li><p>At least 5 years of professional experience specializing in external risk governance or outsourcing oversight.</p></li><li><p>Proven background navigating complex regulatory landscapes within the financial or insurance sectors.</p></li><li><p>Strong technical competency in evaluating third-party service levels and associated operational risks.</p></li><li><p>Highly developed interpersonal skills with a track record of influencing senior leadership and cross-functional teams.</p></li></ul><p> To apply online please use the 'apply' function, alternatively you may contact Lynette Lim. </p><p> (EA: 94C3609/ R1435181 )</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
